name: Pura Melanting
address: Seririt, Jl. Raya Gilimanuk, Banyupoh, Kec. Gerokgak, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81155, Indonesia
review 1: Temple at 2 km away from the main road. Seems to be busy at some time because a lot of stalls and warungs
review 2:
Full of trash. Why don’t you clean up even around a temple? We cleaned up the beach in Pemuteran for five days. Now we know where it comes from…and all the poor scared dogs in bad conditions in the area.
So sad to see. We donated 50.000 for two people and regret it now. So many people are just sitting around, no one use this free time to clean. Sad and disgusting! Would be such a nice place…we would give more stars if they would take more care.
review 3: Beautiful temple with an impressive architecture. The landscape is amazing, too. Very enjoyable! It's quite a calm place as long there are no bigger ceremonies (I didn't see any other tourists). You can borrow a Sarong for a donation of your choice.
review 4: If you're staying in this area make sure to put this temple on your list. The temple is surrounded by beautiful views on the mountains and nature. Tourists should wear a sarong and donate a small amount to get access. The locals were very friendly and asked me to join in on their (Saturday 11:00) prayer. They also said the monkeys were a bit more aggressive (though I wasn't approached by one), so watch out with plastic bags and cameras.
review 5: Amazing! So beautiful. Definitely a must see on your trip.

name: Warung "Bu Ketut" Melanting
address: jl.pura melanting, Banyupoh, Kec. Gerokgak, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81155, Indonesia
